<section class="section section--alt" id="app-stack-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who designs it</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A Certified ProAdvisor designs the stack around your books.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Picking apps is the easy part &mdash; any list will name the popular ones. The work that actually makes a stack hold together is everything underneath: deciding what each app is allowed to post, mapping its sync to the right accounts, turning off the duplicate paths so a sale isn&rsquo;t recorded twice, and reconciling the result against the bank until it ties. A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications does that against a written scope, with the accounting file as the system of record, and confirms each connection posts cleanly before closing. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not any app vendor&rsquo;s support; an Intuit account, login, or billing matter stays with Intuit, and a specific app&rsquo;s in-product support stays with its vendor.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
